comment_data.body:
When I saw this, I thought: what, you take a borrowed reference above and then decref it - how's that a fix? And it took me a while to remember that because we're increfing the type reference in `tp_new()`, you're not intending the decref `tp` here but really `o->ob_type` (which is technically the same but semantically different). I think that's worth a code comment.

Also, don't we need to do the same thing for objects that go to the freelist? Your change only goes into the `else` branch.
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -1865,15 +1865,19 @@ def generate_dealloc_function(self, scope, code):
                 code.putln("} else")
                 code.putln("#endif")
                 code.putln("{")
+            code.putln("PyTypeObject *tp = Py_TYPE(o);")
             code.putln("#if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SLOTS")
             # Asking for PyType_GetSlot(..., Py_tp_free) seems to cause an error in pypy
-            code.putln("(*Py_TYPE(o)->tp_free)(o);")
+            code.putln("(*tp->tp_free)(o);")
             code.putln("#else")
             code.putln("{")
-            code.putln("freefunc tp_free = (freefunc)PyType_GetSlot(Py_TYPE(o), Py_tp_free);")
+            code.putln("freefunc tp_free = (freefunc)PyType_GetSlot(tp, Py_tp_free);")
             code.putln("if (tp_free) tp_free(o);")
             code.putln("}")
             code.putln("#endif")
+            code.putln("#if CYTHON_USE_TYPE_SPECS")
+            code.putln("Py_DECREF(tp);")
+            code.putln("#endif")

comment_data.body:
> Also, don't we need to do the same thing for objects that go to the freelist? Your change only goes into the else branch.

Yes we should.

We're more restrictive than we need to be on freelists for heaptypes so it's surprisingly hard to get one. I'll do a separate PR to relax that.

commit.message: Decref the type object when using heap types
Add comment; decref in freelists too
Handle type references for common types too

Revert "Handle type references for common types too"

This reverts commit def8deb1dd1ead07ae4c2b4abdb0720eec5bd437.

Objects on the freelist should keep a reference to their type

Because it's needed in the freelist cleanup function.
